      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a really solid start. i love how you used words like \"corrective measure\" and \"dismantle\"—it makes it sound much more urgent. \n\ncould you expand on that? specifically, i need to address the \"meritocracy\" argument. a lot of people say that wealth should just be based on hard work and talent, and that redistribution is unfair to those who earned it. can you help me write a section that explains why the meritocracy argument is basically invalid or flawed in the context of racial equity?",
