      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of a pure meritocracy is a dangerous myth that conveniently ignores the starting line fallacy inherent in our society. When racial bias dictates access to quality education, generational housing wealth, and hiring opportunities, \"hard work\" is not an equal playing field. Therefore, the wealth disparities we see are not solely the result of individual effort, but the predictable outcome of systemic racial advantage. Redistribution is simply leveling the playing field that the current system has deliberately tilted.",
      "source": "target",
